# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
To find Island A, two types of solutions are commonly used: Depth-First Search (DFS) and Breadth-First Search (BFS).

Depth-First Search (DFS):

Start from a given cell on the grid and recursively explore its neighboring cells.


Breadth-First Search (BFS):

Start from a given cell on the grid and explore all its neighboring cells at the same distance level before moving on to the next level.
Use a queue to store the cells to be visited.

